ncover the existence of deep family poverty. Further, by exposing the problem of unequal access of children of different classes to schooling, these programs paved the way for education and funding reforms of the next generation. Another consequence was that in their equal treatment of both genders, the laws fostered the more egalitarian language of the war, which faded from other sectors of society, possibly laying groundwork for feminist claims of future decades. The way in which the poorest families influenced the creation of public, educational, and welfare institutions is a dimension of the welfare state unexamined until this book. At a time when the very idea of a universal welfare state is questioned, The Social Origins of the Welfare State considers the fundamental reasons behind its creation and brings to light new perspectives on its future.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAllocations familialesxHistoirex20e sièclexQuébec (Province). 0aChild laborxHistoryx20th centuryxQuébec (Province). 0aChild laborzQuébec (Province)xHistoryy20th century. 0aChild laborzQuébec (Province)xHistoryy20th century. 0aEducation, CompulsoryxHistoryx20th centuryxQuébec (Province). 0aEducation, CompulsoryzQuébec (Province)xHistoryy20th century. 0aEducation, CompulsoryzQuébec (Province)xHistoryy20th century. 0aEnfantsxTravailxHistoirex20e sièclexQuébec (Province). 0aFamilieszQuébec (Province)xHistoryy20th century. 0aFamilieszQuébec (Province)y20th century. 0aFamillexHistoirex20e sièclexQuébec (Province). 0aFamillezQuebec (Province)xHistoirey20e siecle. 0aFamillezQuébec (Province)xHistoirey20e siècle. 0aFamily allowancesxHistoryx20th centuryxQuébec (Province). 0aFamily allowanceszQuébec (Province)xHistoryy20th century. 0aFamily allowanceszQuébec (Province)xHi